Reasoning: The paper proposes a formal definition of intelligence and discusses the practical issues involved in developing a real-world performance metric based on this definition. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper evaluates different artificial agents, which is a common theme in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of universal induction, which is a topic in the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the asymptotic computability of the Universal Intelligence Measure, which is related to the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-category.
